rial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic; font-weight:bold">Appendix B</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Examples of stations serving isolated communities</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Berney Arms</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (Norfolk) on the Wherry Line.  No road access to this isolated community on the Norfolk Broads.  Access by footpath across Halv</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">e</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">rgate marshes or by boat.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Two trains a day each way call on request and five on Sundays.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Causeland </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(Cornwall) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">on the Looe Valley line.  Remote community linked by narrow lanes.  No regular bus service.  Ten trains a day from Liskeard call on request. </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Chathill </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(Northumberland) on East Coast Main Line.  Terminus of local </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">train </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">service from Newcastle twice a day</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  O</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ne bus a week (Thursday) provides a shopping trip to Alnwick (no rail connection). </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Commondale </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(North Yorkshire) on Esk Valley Line.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Serves an isolated community within the North York Moors.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Four trains a day u</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">sed by walkers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and by local residents to a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ccess work and services. One bus a week (Wednesday) provides a shopping trip to Stokesley and Northallerton. Population 179 (2011)</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Corrour</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (Highland Region), on West Highl</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">nd Line.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Ten miles from the nearest public </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">road.  Station accessible by footpath </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">only.  Very isolated</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> but frequented by walkers</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> and visitors</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> to the Station House restaurant</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Served by four trains a day including (on request) the Caledonian Sleeper to London Euston.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Dent</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">North Yorkshire</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">) </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4.5 miles from the village. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Five train servic</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">es each way a day.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Limited bus connection between station and village Saturdays all year, Sundays May to September. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Bus link part funded by Friends of the Settle &amp; Carlisle line.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Population 675 (2001)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  Popular with walkers.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Llang</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">y</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">nllo</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">(Powys)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> on the Heart of Wales line between Shrewsbury and </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Swansea</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  Small and remote rural community with </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">four trains daily each way calling on request (two trains on Sundays)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  Alternative transport is a bookable taxi bus twice a day to and from Knighton.  (No S</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">unday </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">taxi </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">bus service).  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Yeoford</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (Devon)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">on the Tarka Line (Exeter to Barnstaple.)  Village away from main road </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">but has a station with </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> train every hour, which stops on request</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  Alternative public transport is a </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">bus once a week (Fridays only) pr</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">viding a shopping trip to Exeter.  The line’s ‘rail ale train’ encourag</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">es</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> visitors to </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">use the village pub.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">  </span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Yetminster</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt"> (Dorset) on the Heart of Wessex line between Bristol and Weymouth.  Village and nearby Ryme Intrinseca are away from the main road (A37)</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">.  E</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">ight trains a day each way </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">call </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">on request and three to five on Sundays.  </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">F</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">our buses a day to Yeovil and two to Sherborne or Dorchester. (No Sunday buses)</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">September 2013</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>